.TH DEEPIN-TRAFFIC-TOLL 1 "April 2026" "deepin-traffic-toll 1.0.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
deepin-traffic-toll \- Process-level network traffic control tool
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B sudo deepin-traffic-toll
\fI<interface>\fR \fI<config-file>\fR [options]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Deepin Traffic Toll is a C++ implementation of network traffic control tool
using Linux TC (Traffic Control) and HTB (Hierarchy Token Bucket) queue
disciplines to achieve fine-grained bandwidth management for specific applications.

It allows you to set upload/download rate limits for different processes
and assign traffic priorities.
.SH ARGUMENTS
.TP
\fBinterface\fR
The network interface to perform traffic shaping on (e.g., eth0, wlan0).
.TP
\fBconfig-file\fR
Path to the YAML configuration file.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-d\fR, \fB\-\-delay\fR \fIseconds\fR
Process check interval time (default: 1.0 seconds).
.TP
\fB\-l\fR, \fB\-\-logging-level\fR \fIlevel\fR
Log level: TRACE, DEBUG, INFO, SUCCESS, WARNING, ERROR, CRITICAL (default: INFO).
.TP
\fB\-s\fR, \fB\-\-speed-test\fR
Automatically detect upload/download speed.
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Display help information.
.SH REQUIREMENTS
.TP
.B Root privileges
TC operations require root/sudo access.
.TP
.B Linux kernel with TC support
The kernel must support Traffic Control.
.TP
.B IFB kernel module
Intermediate Functional Block module is required for ingress shaping.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Basic usage:
sudo deepin-traffic-toll eth0 /etc/deepin-traffic-toll/limit.yaml
.TP
With custom check interval:
sudo deepin-traffic-toll wlan0 config.yaml --delay 2.0
.TP
With auto speed detection:
sudo deepin-traffic-toll eth0 config.yaml --speed-test
.SH CONFIGURATION
The configuration file uses YAML format. See
.I /etc/deepin-traffic-toll/example.yaml
for a detailed example.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /usr/bin/deepin-traffic-toll
Main executable.
.TP
.I /etc/deepin-traffic-toll/
Configuration directory.
.TP
.I /etc/deepin-traffic-toll/example.yaml
Example configuration file.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR tc (8),
.BR tc-htb (8)
